"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Implement Cursor Agent as External Binary\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe external agent protocol and adapter are already implemented (Steps 1-4 from the previous plan are complete). The built-in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` package has been deleted. Now we need to implement the cursor agent as an external binary (`entire-agent-cursor`) that implements the external agent protocol, keeping it in this repo for now.\\n\\nThe binary will be at `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go` — a standalone Go binary that can be discovered via `$PATH` by the CLI's `external.DiscoverAndRegister()`.\\n\\n## Step 1: Create the Binary Entry Point\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go`\\n\\nA simple `main()` that dispatches subcommands. Since this is a protocol binary (not a user CLI), use a switch on `os.Args[1]` rather than cobra. Parse flags with `flag.NewFlagSet` per subcommand.\\n\\nSubcommands to implement (matching the protocol spec):\\n- `info` — static JSON response\\n- `detect` — check `.cursor/` exists\\n- `get-session-id` — extract from stdin HookInput\\n- `get-session-dir` — compute `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized>/agent-transcripts`\\n- `resolve-session-file` — handle nested vs flat layout\\n- `read-session` — read JSONL from session ref\\n- `write-session` — write native data to session ref\\n- `format-resume-command` — static message\\n- `read-transcript` — read raw bytes\\n- `chunk-transcript` — JSONL line-based chunking (reuse `agent.ChunkJSONL`)\\n- `reassemble-transcript` — JSONL reassembly (reuse `agent.ReassembleJSONL`)\\n- `parse-hook` — dispatch to 7 hook parsers\\n- `install-hooks` — write `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `uninstall-hooks` — remove Entire hooks from `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `are-hooks-installed` — check `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `get-transcript-position` — count JSONL lines\\n- `extract-modified-files` — always returns empty (cursor has no tool_use blocks)\\n- `extract-prompts` — parse JSONL, filter user messages, strip IDE tags\\n- `extract-summary` — find last assistant text block\\n\\n## Step 2: Package Structure\\n\\nSince the binary has significant logic, organize into a package rather than one giant main.go:\\n\\n```\\ncmd/entire-agent-cursor/\\n├── main.go              # Entry point, subcommand dispatch\\n├── cursor.go            # Core logic: detect, session management, path helpers\\n├── hooks.go             # Hook install/uninstall/are-installed logic\\n├── lifecycle.go         # ParseHookEvent: 7 hook parsers\\n├── transcript.go        # TranscriptAnalyzer: position, prompts, summary, modified files\\n└── types.go             # Hook input types, hooks.json types\\n```\\n\\nAll files in `package main`.\\n\\n## Step 3: Reuse Shared Packages\\n\\nThe binary can import shared packages from this repo since it's in the same module:\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent` — `ChunkJSONL`, `ReassembleJSONL`, `HookInput`, `Event`, `EventType`, `AgentSession`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/transcript` — `ParseFromFileAtLine`, `ParseFromBytes`, `ExtractUserContent`, type constants\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/textutil` — `StripIDEContextTags`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil` — `MarshalIndentWithNewline`\\n\\n**Key difference from built-in agent:** The binary communicates via JSON stdout, not Go interfaces. Each subcommand reads args/stdin, does the work, and outputs JSON to stdout.\\n\\n## Step 4: Protocol Response Details\\n\\n### `info` response (static):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\",\\\"session-end\\\",\\\"before-submit-prompt\\\",\\\"stop\\\",\\\"pre-compact\\\",\\\"subagent-start\\\",\\\"subagent-stop\\\"],\\n  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `parse-hook` response:\\nOutputs the `eventJSON` struct (same format as `external/types.go:eventJSON`). For hooks with no lifecycle significance, outputs `null`.\\n\\n### Session/transcript methods:\\nRead/write files using the same logic as the deleted `cursor.go` — session dir at `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-path>/agent-transcripts`, nested vs flat file layout detection.\\n\\n## Step 5: Key Logic to Port\\n\\n### From `cursor.go`:\\n- `sanitizePathForCursor(path)` — strips leading `/`, replaces non-alphanumeric with `-`\\n- `DetectPresence` — check `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` env + `.cursor/` dir exists\\n- `GetSessionDir` — `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized>/agent-transcripts`, with `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR` override\\n- `ResolveSessionFile` — check nested (`dir/id/id.jsonl`) first, fall back to flat (`dir/id.jsonl`)\\n- `ReadSession` — resolve session file, read raw JSONL bytes, return as AgentSession JSON\\n- `WriteSession` — write native data to session ref path\\n\\n### From `hooks.go`:\\n- `InstallHooks` — read/modify `.cursor/hooks.json` using `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields\\n- `UninstallHooks` — remove Entire hook entries from all 7 hook types\\n- `AreHooksInstalled` — check for any Entire hook command prefix\\n- Recognized prefixes: `\\\"entire \\\"` and `\\\"go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go \\\"`\\n\\n### From `lifecycle.go`:\\n- `ParseHookEvent` — switch on hook name, dispatch to 7 parsers\\n- Each parser reads stdin JSON, maps to protocol event JSON\\n- `resolveTranscriptRef` — if transcript path is empty, dynamically compute it from env\\n\\n### From `transcript.go`:\\n- `GetTranscriptPosition` — count lines with bufio.Reader\\n- `ExtractPrompts` — use `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine`, filter TypeUser, extract content, strip IDE tags\\n- `ExtractSummary` — parse all, walk backward for last assistant text block\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — always returns `{\\\"files\\\": null, \\\"current_position\\\": 0}`\\n\\n## Step 6: Tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor_test.go` (and per-file tests)\\n\\nTest the binary end-to-end by:\\n1. Building the binary with `go build`\\n2. Running subcommands and checking JSON output\\n3. Testing hook parsing with sample stdin payloads\\n\\nAlso test individual functions unit-style:\\n- `sanitizePathForCursor` — various path inputs\\n- Hook JSON round-trip preservation\\n- Transcript line counting\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go` — Entry point + subcommand dispatch\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor.go` — Core: detect, session, path helpers\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/hooks.go` — Hook install/uninstall\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/lifecycle.go` — ParseHookEvent dispatching\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/transcript.go` — Transcript analysis\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/types.go` — Type definitions\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor_test.go` — Tests\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n- None (the external adapter and discovery are already in place)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `go build ./cmd/entire-agent-cursor/` — binary compiles\\n2. `./entire-agent-cursor info` — outputs valid info JSON\\n3. `./entire-agent-cursor detect` — checks `.cursor/` presence\\n4. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all pass\\n5. Place binary on PATH, verify `external.DiscoverAndRegister()` discovers it\\n6. Verify `entire hooks cursor ...` subcommands work end-to-end\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/nodo/.claude/projects/-Users-nodo-work-cli/b12319af-9a0a-4691-b084-e5fc5ae7e446.j